annote = {This paper uses field plot data to investigate theories explaining size distributions. It shows that tree abundances do not scale with tree size, but are instead explained by growth and mortality rates. Size distributions are not consistent, and are instead related to variation in growth and mortality. This suggests that to understand size distributions it is important to understand drivers of mortality in large trees. Since growth and mortality are not constant, this indicates that we may see variation in tree size distributions with time in response to drivers of growth and mortality, particularly of large trees.},
